title: Fantastic Friday at Parnell Tower planned
text:
Fantastic Friday at Parnell Tower planned Sheboygan Press Media 11:13 p.m. CDT October 9, 2015 child boy kid reading a book on blue (Photo: Getty Images/iStockphoto) CONNECT TWEET LINKEDIN COMMENT EMAIL MORE 
Plymouth School District Community Education and Recreation Fantastic Friday event on Oct. 16will feature a Parnell Tower adventure for students in kindergarten through eighth grade. 
Fantastic Fridays are offered on teacher in-service days this fall. Supervision is provided by Plymouth School District Community Education and Recreation child-care workers and youth center staff. 
Buses will depart Horizon Elementary School, 411 S. Highland Ave., at 9:30 a.m. and return between 2:30-3:30 p.m. â€” wrap-around child care will be provided between 6 a.m. and 6 p.m. at no additional cost. 
The fee is $45. For more information visit www.plymouth.k12.wi.us, email commedrec@plymouth.k12.wi.us, call 920-892-5068 or visit the Community Education and Recreation office on the north end of Plymouth High School, 125 Highland Ave. Read or Share this story: http://shebpr.es/1RzkVmU TOP VIDEOS
